name: Midnight Gypsy Necklace
description:
This necklace is actually a modification of a necklace that a friend gave me.  The origional necklace had these horribly scratchy black glass beads on it that made wearing the necklace a miserable experience.  So I unstrung the entire necklace, shifted through all of the beads, took out all of those scratchy glass beads and replaced them with a smooth round black glass bead.  And then restrung the entire necklace again.  Needless to say the necklace is much more pleasant to wear now.


Everything I make is made in a smoke free and pet free environment.

name: Periwinkle and Teal Mosaic Ring
description:
Circumference: 2 1/8"

This beautiful ring was beaded by hand using all glass beads.  It was created using a peyote stitch with a bead size increase.

This ring is not as blue as it appears in the pictures.  Purple is a very hard color to represent correctly with unprofessional digital pictures.  Colors may vary according to monitor calibration (you're monitor's color settings).  In real life this ring is true Periwinkle and the band is much more purple then represented in these images.  I tried to adjust the hue for accuracy, however it distorted the images too much when I did so.

Everything I make is made in a smoke free and pet free environment.
